<section class="about-intro">
  <div class="about-intro-content">
    <h1>I'm Aisha Souto-Maior, a Brooklyn native now based in Montpellier.</h1>
    <p>Born and raised in Brooklyn, I've spent the last decade living across Paris, Amsterdam, and now Montpellier.</p>
    <p>I grew up building things with Legos, getting lost in books and people watching around the city. I was always curious about people, how they felt about things, and what made a story or an experience stick with someone. That curiosity eventually led me to Parsons to study interaction design, and I loved it because it was at the intersection of design and computer science.</p>
    <p>For the last 16 years, I've been working in UX research and design, helping teams understand their users and turn complex product challenges into experiences that actually work for the people using them. Previously Lead Designer at <a href="https://skillcrush.com" target="_blank">Skillcrush</a> and Senior UX Designer and team lead at <a href="https://booking.com" target="_blank">Booking.com</a>.</p>
    <p>Since 2021, I've been consulting through Studio Aisha, working with startups, mid to large companies and global nonprofits on research, UX strategy and experience design. I help teams figure out what's actually going on with their users, where the real opportunities are, and how to move forward with clarity and confidence. Collaboration is at the heart of how I work, and I'm at my best when my clients and I are genuinely working as a team.</p>
  </div>
