<section class="experience">
  <h2>Experience</h2>
  
  <article class="job">
    <h3>Studio Aisha</h3>
    <p class="tenure">January 2021 - Current</p>
    <p>I started Studio Aisha to do the kind of work I love, on my own terms. I've worked with individual entrepreneurs, global nonprofits, startups, and mid- to large-size companies on everything from research and UX strategy to information architecture and experience design. What ties it all together is helping teams understand the real problem before moving toward a solution, and working through it together.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="job">
    <h3>Booking.com</h3>
    <p class="tenure">July 2017 - December 2020</p>
    <p>I joined as a UX designer and grew into a senior designer and team lead over nearly four years. Most of my time was spent working closely with product managers and researchers on complex, high-traffic customer journeys, trying to understand the decisions users were making and why, so we could design experiences that actually served what they needed. I learned a lot about how to design strategically across a large system without losing sight of the user.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="job">
    <h3>Skillcrush</h3>
    <p class="tenure">January 2015 - June 2017</p>
    <p>As lead designer, I worked across product, UX, and art direction, leading a small multidisciplinary team. I got to be close to the whole picture there: research, testing, delivery, and making sure everything felt coherent from a brand perspective. I also led the redesign of the learning platform interface and served as subject matter expert for three courses I helped develop, which pushed me to think about the experience from both sides of it.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="job">
    <h3>Penton Media</h3>
    <p class="tenure">November 2010 - July 2014</p>
    <p>I was worked closely with project managers and engineers to design new functionality and layouts for custom Drupal-based CMSs, and was one of two designers responsible for migrating over 80 legacy sites to a new platform. It was fast-paced, detailed work with ever-changing stakeholder requirements, and it's where I really learned to lean into collaboration with developers and PMs as a core part of how I work.</p>
  </article>

